  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.eur.absa.model.DataEntity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Prediction, Relation, Span, Word

    public abstract class DataEntity
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<DataEntity>
    To be implemented by anything that can have annotations. For instance, Word, Span, and SpanRelation all implement Annotatable.

    Kim Schouten

      • getTextualUnit

        public Span getTextualUnit()
        Return the textual unit this Span appears in. By definition, all Words within a Span must originate from the same textual unit. Textual unit can be a document, or basically any piece of independent text. Word order is counted per textual unit.
        Returns:

      • equals

        public boolean equals(DataEntity anotherObject)
        For now it seems that just checking global id's is the most convenient and fast way of determining whether two DataEntities are the same object. Downside is that it is possible to create an exact duplicate of an already existing DataEntity, since, being a new object, it will get its own id value.
